      "stepId": "problem-illustration",
      "mentorSays": "Perfect! Now let's understand what the Longest Palindromic Substring problem is asking.\n\n**Problem Definition:**\nGiven a string s, return the longest palindromic substring in s.\n\nA palindrome reads the same backward as forward.\n\n**Example 1:** s = \"babad\"\nLongest palindromes: \"bab\" or \"aba\"\nAnswer: \"bab\" (or \"aba\")\n\n**Example 2:** s = \"cbbd\"\nLongest palindrome: \"bb\"\nAnswer: \"bb\"\n\n**Key Insight:** For each position, expand around center(s) to find longest palindrome. Handle odd (center at char) and even (center between chars) lengths.",
